# {{ product_name }} — FAQ

## Is this a full SEO audit?

No. {{ product_name }} is a **weekly monitoring and reporting layer**, not a one-time deep SEO audit. It focuses on repeatable checks: availability, basic SEO signals, broken links, forms, changes vs the previous week, and top prioritized actions.

## Is this a replacement for Ahrefs/Semrush?

No. It does not replace backlink databases, keyword research suites, or competitive intelligence tools. It complements them with a **client-ready weekly report** your clients can actually read.

## Do I need to give access to analytics?

Not for the first version. Reports are built from public page checks and your configured scan settings. You can add analytics context manually in your delivery email if needed.

## Can I send reports under my own brand?

Yes. Reports support white-label branding: agency name, client name, colors, logo, and footer text.

## How often are reports generated?

Designed for a **weekly cadence** — one report per site per week, with change tracking vs the previous stored check.

## Can I start with one website?

Yes. The Starter plan is for a single website. You can upgrade when you add more clients.

## What happens if the site is down?

The report records availability status and surfaces it in the health score and warnings. You can follow up with the client the same week.

## Is email delivery automatic?

Email is **optional**. The default workflow prepares reports and outbox drafts; you review and send manually. Automatic sending requires explicit SMTP configuration and `send` mode.

## Can reports be reviewed before sending?

Yes. That is the recommended workflow: generate report → review HTML/PDF → send when ready.
